The legendary, family-controlled leather
goods house is contemplating an unprecedented and decidedly old-school move=
: couture. Do the costs and craft required for this rarefied market make se=
nse for the already stellar quarter-trillion-dollar business?

Lauren Sherman ( https://puck.news/author/lauren-sherman/?utm_campaign=3DLi=
ne+Sheet+-+IC+SUBS+%281%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+IC+SUBS+%281=
%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3D=
f6c60617da42abd12a )
Lauren Sherman ( https://puck.news/author/lauren-sherman/?utm_campaign=3DLi=
ne+Sheet+-+IC+SUBS+%281%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+IC+SUBS+%281=
%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3D=
f6c60617da42abd12a )

In fashion, we often say that there is
Herm=C3=A8s, and then there is everyone else. The 186-year-old firm doesn=
=E2=80=99t play by the rules of luxury, it makes them=E2=80=94setting stand=
ards in terms of pricing, distribution, and quality, etcetera. Herm=C3=A8s =
famously doesn=E2=80=99t have a marketing department or hire celebrities to=
 front its advertising campaigns.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Herm=C3=A8s also refuses to charge what the market would bear for its prici=
est handbags. That=E2=80=99s a
pointed tactic that has nestled the company, controlled by the same family =
for six generations, in the good graces of consumers while still profiting =
handsomely. Herm=C3=A8s made about $15 billion in 2023, which is peanuts co=
mpared to LVMH=E2=80=99s $86 billion, but it had a comparatively advantaged=
 43.49 percent operating profit compared to LVMH=E2=80=99s 26.5 percent. Th=
is spread explains, in part, how its $244 billion market cap is around 75 p=
ercent of LVMH=E2=80=99s own $329 billion valuation.

=C2=A0

Since Herm=C3=A8s does what it wants, my interest was piqued when I heard r=
ecently that the company was plotting an expansion into a category historic=
ally devoid of new entrants...=C2=A0

